      • setUseWideViewPort

        public void setUseWideViewPort(boolean use)
        Sets whether the XWalkView should enable support for the "viewport" HTML meta tag or should use a wide viewport. When the value of the setting is false, the layout width is always set to the width of the XWalkView control in device-independent (CSS) pixels. When the value is true and the page contains the viewport meta tag, the value of the width specified in the tag is used. If the page does not contain the tag or does not provide a width, then a wide viewport will be used.
        Parameters:
        use - whether to enable support for the viewport meta tag.
        Since:
        6.0

      • getUseWideViewPort

        public boolean getUseWideViewPort()
        Gets whether the XWalkView supports the "viewport" HTML meta tag or will use a wide viewport.
        Returns:
        true if the XWalkView supports the viewport meta tag.

      • setSupportZoom

        public void setSupportZoom(boolean support)
        Sets whether the XWalkView should support zooming using its on-screen zoom controls and gestures. The particular zoom mechanisms that should be used can be set with setBuiltInZoomControls(boolean). This setting does not affect zooming performed using the zoomIn() and zoomOut() methods. The default is true.
        Parameters:
        support - whether the XWalkView should support zoom.
        Since:
        6.0

      • supportZoom

        public boolean supportZoom()
        Gets whether the XWalkView supports zoom.
        Returns:
        true if the XWalkView supports zoom.
        Since:
        6.0

      • setBuiltInZoomControls

        public void setBuiltInZoomControls(boolean enabled)
        Sets whether the XWalkView should use its built-in zoom mechanisms. The built-in zoom mechanisms comprise on-screen zoom controls, which are displayed over the XWalkView's content, and the use of a pinch gesture to control zooming. Whether or not these on-screen controls are displayed can be set with setDisplayZoomControls(boolean). The default is false.
        Parameters:
        enabled - whether the XWalkView should use its built-in zoom mechanisms.
        Since:
        6.0
